commit.message:
Dataset populator (#13)

* Created script to read and write to dataset via user input through terminal

* working sample json array to csv converter

* Bug Fixes

* Updated to add blank rows for each field that needs to be rated for each tweet

* Added date parameter and header comment/description

* Received and converted Json objects from Twitter API to CSV format

* Small edits and fixes

* Changed so that it appends and doesn't append the headers if te file isn't empty

* Completed sorter that sorts csv file by whether they are positive or negative and writes sorts the dataset into the format that can be fed to the model

* Updated dataset_populator with new fields and the ability to quit process without losing progress.

* Moved some data into correct folders, fixed issue with dataset_populator losing last tweet before quitting.

* extended the sorting to all three fields that are evaluated by the model; fixed some parts and added count on top of the file

* Used dataset_populator.py to complete a data set

* Updated I/O format of dataset_populator to make it easier to use

* updated tweets-json-to-csv.py to delete tweets.json after running to prevent suplication of data.

* small fixes

* fixed data_setpopulator so that it has no \n when writing a new line

* Added script to remove all newline characters from tweets.json before is it parsed by tweets-to-csv.py to solve issue with sorting/counting algorithm.

* fixed bug that causes the sorting method to pop one more line of csv data than it should have

* Rewrote csv_to_fields.py more pythonically (for clarity), renamed files with snakecase.

* Moved dataset_populator.py into CSV/ directory

* Fix for a possible problem?

* Merged to /develop

Co-authored-by: Boheng2 <43503597+Boheng2@users.noreply.github.com>
